Good food if a bit pricy. Quality and variety reduced since they gave up dinners. Always call for reservations because they sometimes have a big party and then lots of food goes quickly. Try the ahi poke tacos (4 is best price) and the lilikoi cheesecake dessert. You cannot go wrong with those.

Been several years since eating here. Love the ambience; had an opportunity to dine here with my wife following a late morning appointment in town. Service was slow and it wasn't busy at all. Selected the Chinese chicken salad along with the furukake french fries. Not enough dressing on the salad and the fries were a bit soggy .

Let's face it, Cafe Julua is the go to place in downtown for a business lunch. Good food, good service, a little pricey but you can't beat the ambiance. It loses one star from me for the lunchtime noise level. It used to be easier to have a conversation over lunch there, but today it was a bit louder than I recall in the past. Still, I'll go back.

Always great service and food.  Annie always gives us the best service n her smile and personality are priceless!!

I love this old building, it's where I learned to swim. Cafe Julia is beautiful, stately an oasis in downtown. The food is excellent with a few exceptions. I had the veggie quiche with cream of garlic soup and a salad. The quiche and salad were excellent but the soup was garlicky yet bland, no finish, no spice or salt, just garlic. Needed something more...

I've been here for lunches and a number of events. It's a beautiful space for an event -- especially when the weather is good and you set up in the courtyard. They've had a number of rotating chefs over the years and some were def better than others. The current food I had at an event was well executed though. I always wish I could eat here during the work week but it takes a little longer than I'd like for my limited lunch hour sometimes. It also gets pretty warm inside around noon. It's one of the few sit-down places with service left in downtown though so good for lunch meetings or for special occasions.
Food is excellent.. Nice place for lunch..
Love this restaurant! Wonderful food and service!

There is nothing about this wedding venue that isn’t PERFECT!!! 1. It’s beautiful!!!!!! The architecture, the plants, the string lights!! It’s a fairy tale in the middle of Honolulu. All of the tables and chairs and set-up are included, so you don’t have to worry about it! Who does that these days?! CAFÉ JULIA DOES!!! 2. The staff are incredible! Keli’i, the wedding/event coordinator, is the best!!!! He is seriously the easiest and nicest person to work with! Keli’i was super accommodating, and he handled my frantic bride questions with a smile :) During the event, all of the staff were so nice!! It just made the whole event super fun. 3. THE FOOD! Omg the food!!! I can’t pick a favorite dish, because everything was incredible! All of our guests have said how delicious the food was, and our great aunts (who usually don’t eat very much) went back for thirds! Seriously, I’m still dreaming about that food. I can’t thank Café Julia enough! Our wedding was even more perfect and wonderful and beautiful than I could have imagined :)

Conveniently located right across I'olani Palace. Certainly not a budget place, but not overpriced. The n.a. mixer I had was a little too sweet formy taste.

Our favorite place for lunch in downtown. I especially enjoy the salmon ochazuke and pork chop. Staff are friendly and attentive. The restaurant is located in YWCA and street parking or at Alii Place. We love their lilikoi cheese cake and chocolate mousse.
(Translated by Google) The shrimp are very delicious.  (Original) 海老がとても美味しい。
The burger was satisfying but the customer service is what will really stick out in my mind when I think of Cafe Julia!

$21.95 for a loco Moco. Served over fried rice. At this price I almost expected to be asked what rarity I wanted, but I wasn't. So I thought it would be amazing fried rice; frozen peas and carrots, oddly sweet I don't know if it's from the tsukemono or not. The hamburger was firm solid couldn't detect any filler and the gravy was good, just all the good points were overshadowed by the fried rice mostly.  Ate some garlic fries off my sister's plate, which I liked, was covered furikake.  Can of soda is $4.75.  Ambience is nice, calm, and service was good. Never once had to ask to have my water refilled. I just can't give it more because of the rice.

We stumbled across this restaurant when looking for The Iolani Palace in Honolulu. It is part of the YWCA, and the architecture of both places creates wonderful cool spaces to retreat to when the tropical heat gets too much. The food is delicious too.

Let me start by saying... PARKING IS LIMITED. Cafe Julia is not open for dinner every day- but rather- every OTHER day. It is locally owned and operated. The atmosphere at night is like a hidden-in-the-back-of-an-alley in Rome type of feel...  Stringy lights and live music are the focal points of this fabulous locale. Beau and I visited this place on two occasions-- the first while checking out the place as a possible venue for our WEDDING!!! (Yes, ladies and gents-- he bought the cow!!)... The second time we came,  we went for dinner to get an idea about the catering/food situation FOR the wedding... Aaaaand to see what it looked like at night.  The lights and arches at night do not disappoint.  The rental fee for the venue is $1k on a week day and $3k on the weekend. I like the weekday price, don't you?!  In those prices, the lights, locale, chivari chairs,  set up and break down from ceremony to reception is included. The linens, dinnerware and silverware, also.  Very convenient if you don't want your family members and friends on your special day moving chairs and tables! However,  you have to cater through them. Which is why beau and I tried dinner here-- to see what we liked.  As for me,  the cheesy garlic bread was the best thing ever. Nothing else stuck with me to be honest.  The presentation and entertainment were great but as for our wedding,  beau and I went with another venue.
"We got the spicy broth, and I grabbed 4 plates of the enoki mushrooms."

This place is a hidden gem that is in need of discovery. This was my second visit, first time was of a result of a Groupon. The ambience is pleasing and if you arrive early enough, they do have live music. Annie the server was excellent, and made thoughtful and excellent recommendations.  I started with the Foie, I didn't know what to expect. It it tasted delicious. I selected the Lamb with garlic mash based on Annie's recommendations so wasn't disappointed. Finished the evening with a delicious Bread Pudding, it wasn't sickly sweet, but light. Thanks Cafe Julia for an excellent meal.
Great food. Comfortable ambience.

Lovely restaurant tucked away downtown.  Awesome ambience, live music is also available. We enjoyed a jazz instrumentalist on our evening.  To our delight, the dining area although enclosed does have grills which allows a cool breeze to pass through and feels like you're sitting out in the open.  Nice to have a restaurant open for dinner when most places are closed downtown.  We enjoyed our meal and had the ahi poke tacos, cheesy garlic bread, and foie gras for starters. Entrees were garlic ahi, filet mignon, and the prime rib. Nicely cooked and portions are decent for the price.

I stumbled on this place after my tour of Iolani Palace. Beautiful building. Open air courtyard with shaded tables is lovely. The dining room looks fantastic too. Food is delicious though a bit pricey. (To me...everything on Oahu is expensive.) I grabbed a coupon off Groupon and stopped in for lunch. My coupon wasn't good until dinner but i decided to eat anyways. I got the Ahi Poke tacos. Since it's raw fish I was hesitant, but they were great! Then I returned for dinner and ordered Shrimp Scampi linguini. Also great. Wonderful flavor and good-sized portions. Only complaint I can come up with is that you can hear traffic. But it's the middle of the city so no getting around that. At the moment, the noise is covered by smooth jazz music from the live musician in the corner. All around its a beautiful, classy restaurant.
Great indoor courtyard atmosphere. I had the Lilikoi Cheesecake. Super delicious.
We stumbled in here on a whim, and its amazing. Nice coury yard, quiet, great staff.
